Quote:  I was present at both the tin-kettling and the presentation [to the new bride of a chamber-pot filled with salt and tied about with a wideish ribbon ... with a large bow tied in it ... with the advice that if they used up all of the salt in the chamber-pot they would have Good Luck.] which probably took place between 1925 and 1930.
